.TH add_gui_text  22.14 "Fri Oct 06 02:12:27 2023" 
.SH Name \fBadd_gui_text\fR \-  Adds text (annotation) to the specified custom layer
.SH Syntax \fBadd_gui_text\fR   [-help]  -label <text>  -layer <layerName>   {-box {<x1 y1 x2 y2>} | {{-height <height> | -fixed_height <fixHeight>} -pt {<x y>}  [-orient <direction>]}}  [-box {<x1 y1 x2 y2>} [-no_bbox]] 
.P Adds text (annotation) to the specified custom layer. You can use the add_gui_text command at any point in the design flow. The text added by the command annotates comment text and does not show up in a DEF output.
.P Note: In OpenAccess flows, any text added with the add_gui_text command is stored in the OpenAccess cellview. However, the text is stored in a private structure that is accessible only to Innovus. To create text that is visible in Virtuoso as well, use the add_text command instead.  
.SH  Parameters   "\fB-help\fR" Prints a brief description that includes type and default information for each add_gui_text parameter.  For a detailed description of the command and all of its parameters, use the man command:  man add_gui_text  "\fB-box {<x1 y1 x2 y2>}\fR" Specifies the coordinates of the rectangle in which text will be added. The coordinate values are specified in microns. When this parameter is used, the tool figures out the correct size and orientation to be used to fit the text into the box. The text is center justified in the box.  Use this parameter to control the text orientation and size.  "\fB-height <height>\fR" Specifies the height of the text in microns.  "\fB-fixed_height <fixHeight>\fR" Specifies the height in pixels. <fixHeight> should be an integer value.   "\fB-label <text>\fR" Specifies the text to be displayed. If your text has spaces, enclose it in quotation marks or braces.  "\fB-layer <layerName>\fR" Specifies the GUI layer name to use or create for the text.  If the specified layer does not exist, it will be automatically created.  "\fB-no_bbox\fR" Specifies that bounding box should not be drawn when text is displayed at the specified box coordinates. This parameter can be used only when -box is specified.   "\fB-orient <direction>\fR" Specifies the orientation of the text. Possible values are:   MX MX90 MY MY90 R0 R90 R180 R270  This option cannot be used with -box.  "\fB-pt {<x y>}\fR" Specifies the origin coordinate of the text (microns). 
.SH Examples
.RS  "*" 2 The following command adds the text label Sample Text Display with size of 18 pixels on layer 1 at the specified point coordinates:  add_gui_text -layer 1 -label "Sample Text Display" -fixed_height 18 -pt {0 250}  (<Image> To view the image, refer to the Innovus Text Command Reference - Release 22.1 manual.)  "*" 2 The following command adds the text label Sample Text Display on layer 1 in a box with the specified coordinates. As the length of the box is more than the width, the text is displayed horizontally:  add_gui_text -layer 1 -box {0 250 500 450} -label "Sample Text Display"  (<Image> To view the image, refer to the Innovus Text Command Reference - Release 22.1 manual.)  "*" 2 The following command adds the text label Sample Text Display on layer 1 in a box with the specified coordinates. As the height of the box is more than the width, the text is displayed vertically:  add_gui_text -layer 1 -box {0 250 200 750} -label "Sample Text Display"  (<Image> To view the image, refer to the Innovus Text Command Reference - Release 22.1 manual.)  "*" 2 The following command adds the text label Sample Text Display on layer 1 at the specified box coordinates. However, the bounding box is not displayed:  add_gui_text -layer 1 -box {0 250 500 450} -no_bbox -label "Sample Text Display"  (<Image> To view the image, refer to the Innovus Text Command Reference - Release 22.1 manual.) 
.RE 
.SH Related Information
